pd_0_com_0text: In the wake of the Tsewdim Nuclear Explosion of 2025, the kingdom of Acirema was finally beginning to flourish once again.
pd_1_com_0text:
July 19, 2030 
Much of the Tsewdim remains a barren desert, but many people, left destitute by the aftermath of the explosion, established small settlements.
pd_4_com_0text: Millions died in the explosion and more followed suit due to the residual radiation that seemed to permeate all of the Tsewdim.
pd_5_com_0text: However, our story begins with Cire of Wenkory, a miserable soon-to-be freshman at Wenkory University.
pd_6_com_0text:
July 4th, 2030
Acceptance Letter: Wenkory University (WYU)
Congratulations! On behalf of Wenkory University, I am pleased to announce your admission for Fall 2030!
pd_7_com_0text:
Cire, we’re excited to have you join our Class of 2036! 
Welcome to Wenkory University! 
Tuition: $592,000.19
Due September 1st, 2030
pd_8_com_0text:
Sincerely,
Ivan Safrin
Director of Admissions
pd_9_com_0text: I got in?! I GOT IN!
pd_12_com_0text: Cire checks his bank account. It shows a remaining balance of $24.51. All the previous purchases show that he spent all his money on anime figurines. What a disgusting weeaboo.
pd_13_com_0text: I can’t pay this in two months! But I have to go to school! Why is WYU the only college in this country?
pd_14_com_0text: There are 38 colleges in Acirema (63 before the Explosion). All of them belong to Wenkory University.
pd_15_com_0text: Want to make $592,000.20 fast? Try your hand at the Great Acireman Race hosted by the Prince of Ainor Filac today!
pd_16_com_0text: Team up with 2 others to find the clues along the way to Ainor Filac! The first team with every clue wins. Each member will receive $592,000.20! Meet us at the Lemmik Building for more information in two hours!
pd_17_com_0text: I guess that’s my only hope.
pd_18_com_0text: There’s hundreds of people in the room, listening to the presentation. Cire scopes out who appears to be the best competitors. If he wants a shot at winning, he's going to have to find the best of the best.
pd_20_com_0text: Okay, everyone! Find your teammates and form your teams!
pd_21_com_0text: The teams form so quickly it’s almost comical. Cire’s left teamless in the middle with an old woman and some weird person in a cactus suit. Cire can feel a pang of pain in both his wallet
pd_22_com_0text: Hey kid. Looks like you’re stuck with us.
pd_25_com_0text: Your first hint lies in the domain with the street of many crooks! Good luck to you all!
pd_26_com_0text: The race begins, and after travelling for a few days the party is ambushed by a group of S’Necks.
pd_27_com_0text: Hiss Hiss Hiss! (We heard a whole lotta people are trying to cross our lands for some cash! Sorry, but we’ll be ones the getting rich when we loot your bodies!)
pd_28_com_0text: The party realizes that they’ll have to defeat them if they want to proceed. Who knows why S’Necks would even want money, but here they are, robbing Cire and his goons.
pd_29_com_0text: After defeating the S’Necks, the party comes across the first checkpoint, in Awoi.
pd_30_com_0text: Cire’s team finally find S’Neck Alley, buried deep in the depths of the largest city in Awoi, Turlingbon.
pd_31_com_0text: I remember S’Neck Alley. I fought many gangs here back in my day.
pd_33_com_0text: Hisssssssssssssssssssss! (There’s another reason why it’s called s’neck alley, idiots!)
pd_34_com_0text: Cire’s team discover a suspicious looking dumpster within the Alley. It is completely obvious that the next hint is in there.
pd_35_com_0text: At the speed of light, Nora’s pointer finger flies to her nose. Cactus Kid’s costumed arm does the same.
pd_39_com_0text: Cire dives into the dumpster, searching for a good 10 minutes before he finds the slip of paper at the bottom.
pd_40_com_0text: Haha, you thought the hint was in the dumpster? Try looking at the wall to the RIGHT of the dumpster.
pd_41_com_0text: Go to the land of the loneliest star. Seek the man named Masno H Tsou.
pd_42_com_0text: I only have a month left before tuition is due. Better hurry up and find the next clue.
pd_43_com_0text: The team finds a quiet watering hole to get a drink and some information.
pd_44_com_0text: Bartender, would you possibly know who Masno H Tsou is?
pd_45_com_0text: SHHH, keep your voice down, boy! Say that name around here again and you won’t see the sun tomorrow. He’s a dangerous man, that Tsou. Now get outta here, I don’t need you scarin’ the rest of my customers off.
pd_46_com_0text: Kicked out of the saloon, they set up camp for the night a few hundred meters away. Cire’s sitting on a stump reading from his book while Cactus Kid’s standing next to a cactus. They seem to be having a deep conversation without words.
pd_47_com_0text: Cheer up children, the S’Neck stew’s almost done! Come get your bowls!
pd_48_com_0text: Nora begins ladeling the savory stew into a bowl when she hears a noise.
pd_51_com_0text: A bullet flies, just barely grazing Cire’s cheek. Cire lets out a squeak and falls backwards.
pd_52_com_0text: Heard you been lookin’ for me.
pd_53_com_0text: Within the cowboy hat of the S’Neck leader Masno, Cactus Kid finds a slip of paper.
pd_55_com_0text: What’s that, Kid? You found something? Give it here.
pd_56_com_0text: The next clue lies where the scholar becomes the hedonist.
pd_59_com_0text: Aren’t you too young to know about that?
pd_61_com_0text: Oooh, Adaven! Let me try my hand at the slot machines!
pd_62_com_0text: I can see the Wolly Hood sign! We’re so close! I CAN AFFORD TO GO TO COLLEGE!
pd_64_com_0text: It’s not over yet kid, I can feel something coming.
pd_66_com_0text: From the bushes appears a King Shydra. He blushes a little.
pd_67_com_0text: Maybe I could just get my tuition money here…
pd_68_com_0text: After a few hours of gambling, Nora has not won anything.
pd_69_com_0text: Is this machine rigged?! I’ve been at it for hours and haven’t won a dime! Who runs this place anyway?
pd_70_com_0text: Well-dressed S’Necks slither from the shadows.
pd_71_com_0text: Hiss Hiss? (Does there seem to be a problem, miss?)
pd_72_com_0text: This Casino is run by S’Necks?
pd_73_com_0text: I bet they rigged these machines! Let’s pummel them!
pd_75_com_0text: After the fight, Cactus Kid decides to play the slots before they leave the casino.
pd_78_com_0text: A slip of a paper is deposited from the machine, which is the next hint.
pd_79_com_0text: H-hisss. (You guys are so weak I’m getting secondhand embarrassment.)
pd_81_com_0text: Let’s grab the crown and book it to the Prince. I need to pay tuition soon.
pd_82_com_0text: Oh. You actually made it. Well, congrats. Give me my hats.
pd_83_com_0text: Cire hands over a smelly beanie, Masno’s cowboy hat, the casino owner S’Necks’ fedora, and the King Shydra’s crown.
pd_84_com_0text: Splendid. Here are your checks. Oh, and Cire, is it? I heard that you’re actually an upcoming student at my university?
pd_85_com_0text: Wonderful, fantastic! Well, seeing as you’ll probably need more money to pay for tuition next year, I expect you’ll be collecting more items for me next year. I do need some new shoes.
pd_87_com_0text: You’ve collected the last hint! Finish your travels to Ainor Filac to receive the grand prize!
